{
  "stem": "26142.5",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we introduced ourselves, and we talked to him.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We said, are there more Jews?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He says, no, he is alone.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "His daughter, he was lamenting that his daughter left with the retreating Russian army, because she was a communist official during the two years that the Russians-- from '39 to '41-- that the Russians were there.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So she was afraid to stay behind, and he was lamenting that he is alone, left all alone.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Of course, we saw that this man is of no help to us.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He can't do anything for us.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I remember just asking him, why is there so many flies here?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he was kind of talking to himself saying, the war, the war, the war.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So the two of us walked out of there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Hungry we were, really plenty, because whatever food we had, we didn't want to-- we kept the food for the children.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And on the fields, the fields were-- this is an area where-- it's an agrarian area.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was a lot of corn and wheat.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was already cut and put in bundles, but when the war broke out everything was left, and those were what the Russians call [NON-ENGLISH], so there was no direct ownership on that.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we went out on one of those fields with my brother, Tsvi, and I, and we started taking some-- rubbing with our fingers.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We rubbed some corn, and we rubbed some of the kernels from wheat.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we sat there for an hour or two, I don't remember exactly.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We ate some of these, and then we took up and we went back to the place where my brother Moishe was.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And of course we told them that we found that Jew and we ate already.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
